      "message": "FWIW I\u0027m fairly sure that the behaviour documented at https://pkg.go.dev/bufio#SplitFunc could not be implemented if the scanner issued more reads than strictly necessary, because Read can block arbitrarily, so if we were using Scanner on a pipe, for example, and we read beyond a token, we could block even though there\u0027s a token available. Apart from anything else, that would be a badly breaking change.\n\nSo I think we are OK to rely on these semantics, but given that the code is no longer, I\u0027m OK with this change.",
